{
  "texts": [
    "To establish a baseline, they utilized a gazetteer, contextual patterns, and an existing English NER model.",
    "The authors explored on NE recognition for Indian Languages reveals variations across different languages which is having more extensive work compared to others like Telugu, Marathi and Hindi.",
    "Pant et al. [47] investigated the feasibility of developing a chatbot that can communicate in Kumaon language and possible difficulties that could come up during the method.",
    "Additionally, the authors also gave a thorough analysis of the language and the mapping of it into other languages to make the use of Kumaon's application in industrial processing which is easier to accessible.The authors used the hybrid model which contains machine learning algorithm and rule-based algorithm as it provides best results for Kumauni Languages.",
    "Krishnan et al. [104] presented a new method for semi-automatically creating annotated data sets in order to rapidly prototype named object recognizers."
  ]
}